
Description of the input files:

 - init_PAPASTATION_m06d15.nc
File to initialize the simulation
This file contains temperature and salinity to start the simulation (June,15 2010).
It is deduced from Observation data at PAPA station and completed with Levitus2009 climatology

 - chlorophyll_PAPASTATION.nc
Climatologic file of the surface chlorophyll concentration (usefull in traqsr).
This file come from ORCA025 file at the PAPA point. deduced from Seawifs climatology

 - forcing_PAPASTATION_1h_y2010.nc
Forcing fluxes at the PAPA station for the years 2010.

 - forcing_PAPASTATION_1h_y2011.nc
Forcing fluxes at the PAPA station for the years 2011.





Example of a script (run.ksh) to launch the reference simulation (to be launch in EXP00 directory):
#!/bin/ksh

## ======================================================================
## Path ... should be completed
## ======================================================================
MAINPATH=??????????             # path of NEMO trunk

DIR_ARCHI_INIT=????????????     # PATH for the initial condition file
DIR_ARCHI_FORC=????????????     # PATH for the forcing input files


## ======================================================================
## =======  Nothing to be changed bellow this line  =====================
## ======================================================================

mkdir rundir
cd rundir
## ======================================================================
## file needed for the run
## ======================================================================
cp ${MAINPATH}/NEMOGCM/CONFIG/SHARED/namelist_ref . 
cp ../*.xml            .
cp ../namelist_cfg     .
cp ../opa              .

## ======================================================================
## Climatology of temperature and chlorophyll
## ======================================================================
ln -s ${DIR_ARCHI_INIT}/init_PAPASTATION_m06d15.nc  ./init_PAPASTATION_m06d15.nc
ln -s ${DIR_ARCHI_INIT}/chlorophyll_PAPASTATION.nc  ./chlorophyll.nc

## ======================================================================
## Atmospherical forcings
## ======================================================================
ln -s ${DIR_ARCHI_FORC}/forcin* .

./opa






